The geode server's config is included in the helm/ericsson-nrf-release/values/values_geode.yaml, which is the value of key "cache_xml"
! Notice that !
1. When modify the value of cache_xml, be careful with the indent, align with yaml
2. It is strongly suggest that the designer do remove the extra empty line in the values_geode.yaml
The reason is that, the yaml has strict limit on the space and indent.


The geode client's config is in $ROOT/helm/ericsson-nrf-release/charts/nrf-dbproxy-configmap/config directory.


start goede server locally:
  gfsh run --file=start.gfsh
  gfsh run --file=stop.gfsh


ENVs to run:
export GEODE_DBPROXY_GRPC_PORT=50051
export GEODE_LOCATOR_SERVICENAME=127.0.0.1
export GEODE_LOCATOR_SERVICEPORT=10334
export GEODE_DBPROXY_CLIENT_CONF_PATH="/home/pdu/dev/nrf/helm/ericsson-nrf-release/charts/nrf-dbproxy-configmap/config/cache.xml"
export GEODE_REGION_NFPROFILE="ericsson-nrf-nfprofiles"
export GEODE_REGION_SUBSCRIPTION="subscription-region"
export GEODE_LOG_LEVEL="DEBUG"
export DBPROXY_GRPC_PORT=50051
export DBPROXY_GEODE_CACHE_CONF="/home/pdu/dev/nrf/helm/ericsson-nrf-release/charts/nrf-dbproxy-configmap/config/cache.xml"
export DBPROXY_CONF="/home/pdu/dev/nrf1/db_proxy/config/dbproxy.conf.json"
export LOG4J_CONFIGURATION_FILE="/home/pdu/dev/nrf/helm/ericsson-nrf-release/charts/nrf-dbproxy-configmap/config/nrf-mgmt-log4j2.xml"

